caption: I don’t even know where to start. I asked for a crayola themed birthday cake. Provided a picture of what I wanted. The day of pick up the cake must of been sitting out for too long that the cake literally slid slanted. And not to mention looked NOTHING like the picture I asked for. When I called, the rude baker said “well I can’t bake you another cake for today or give you a refund” and hung up. Worst customer service ever! The owner was not in at the time I called and no one was able to help. Luckily my husband found a bakery that was able to frost a last minute cake for us for my daughters birthday party.

Mi Casa replaced an old time Irish Bakery, but they hold up the tradition of reasonably priced baked goods. They offer staples ranging from bagels, cakes, to cannolis. I would say that the quality is good for the value. You can walk away with a cannoli for less than a buck, try swinging that on Mulberry Street in Little Italy!  The bakery accepts credit cards and offers friendly service. There's limited seating available inside in a non-covid world. This is definitely not a place I would bring a laptop and plan on plugging away at a paper or a Zoom call. The dining space feels a bit cramped.
